Module: vioinput.sys — virtio-input device driver. Surfaces input
events from a virtio-input device (keyboard / mouse / tablet) and
forwards them into the NT 3.5 keyboard/mouse class drivers via the
older IOCTL_INTERNAL_KEYBOARD_CONNECT / IOCTL_INTERNAL_MOUSE_CONNECT
model. Links against the shared virtio.lib (NTOS/VIRTIO).

QEMU device: virtio-keyboard-pci, virtio-mouse-pci, virtio-tablet-pci
(modern only — vendor 0x1AF4 device 0x1052).

!ENDIF

MAJORCOMP=ntos
MINORCOMP=dd

TARGETNAME=vioinput
TARGETPATH=$(BASEDIR)\public\sdk\lib
TARGETTYPE=DRIVER

INCLUDES=..\..\inc;..\..\virtio\inc

TARGETLIBS=$(BASEDIR)\public\sdk\lib\*\virtio.lib

SOURCES=vioinput.c \
        vioinput.rc
